- `IntStream.range(1, 100)` generates a stream of integers from 1 to 99.
- `filter(i -> i > givenValue)` filters the integers in the stream to include only those greater than the given value.
- `forEach(System.out::println)` prints the filtered integers to the console.

You can replace `5` with any integer to print integers greater than that value.

Alternatively, you can use `IntStream.generate` to generate a stream of integers starting from a given number, but this approach is less efficient for large ranges.

